Class Operators

    • com.github.dm.jrt.operator.Operators

      • append

        @NotNull
public static <DATA> InvocationFactory<DATA,DATA> append(@Nullable
                                                                  Channel<?,? extends DATA> channel)
        Returns a factory of invocations appending the outputs returned by the specified channel to the invocation ones.

        Note that the passed channel will be bound as a result of the call, so, in order to support multiple invocations, consider wrapping the channel in a replayable one, by calling the Channels.replay(Channel) utility method.

        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        channel - the output channel.
        Returns:
        the invocation factory instance.

      • appendAccept

        @NotNull
public static <DATA> InvocationFactory<DATA,DATA> appendAccept(long count,
                                                                        @NotNull
                                                                        Consumer<? super Channel<DATA,?>> outputsConsumer)
        Returns a factory of invocations appending the outputs returned by the specified consumer to the invocation ones.
        The result channel will be passed to the consumer, so that multiple or no results may be generated.
        The consumer will be called count number of times only when the routine invocation completes. The count number must be positive.
        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        count - the number of generated outputs.
        outputsConsumer - the consumer instance.
        Returns:
        the invocation factory instance.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified count number is 0 or negative.
        See Also:
        Sequences

      • collect

        @NotNull
public static <DATA> InvocationFactory<DATA,DATA> collect(@NotNull
                                                                   BiConsumer<? super DATA,? super DATA> accumulateConsumer)
        Returns a factory of invocations accumulating data through the specified consumer.

        The output will be computed as follows: 

        
 consumer.accept(acc, input);
        where the initial accumulated value will be the the first input.
        The accumulated value will be passed as result only when the invocation completes.
        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        accumulateConsumer - the bi-consumer instance.
        Returns:
        the invocation factory instance.

                                                                  @NotNull

      • groupBy

        @NotNull
public static <DATA> InvocationFactory<DATA,List<DATA>> groupBy(@NotNull
                                                                         Function<DATA,Object> keyFunction)
        Returns a factory of invocations grouping the input data in collections where all the data correspond to the same key.
        The returned keys will be compared for equalities by employing the equals() method.

        Given a numeric sequence of inputs starting from 0, and a key function returning the modulo 2 of such numbers, the final output will be: 

        
 => [(0, 2, 4, 6, 8, ..., N), (1, 3, 5, 7, 9, ..., N + 1)]

        Note that the groups will be produced only after the invocation completes.
        Note also that the group order is not guaranteed.

        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        keyFunction - the function returning a key object for each input.
        Returns:
        the invocation factory instance.

        @NotNull

 => [0, 1, 2, 3, 4]
